The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Actor dead
                                                                                                               Actor dead
                            
	London, March 20 (AP): Paul Scofield, a towering British stage actor who won international fame and a Oscar for the film A Man for All Seasons, has died, his agent said today. He was 86.        
	Agent Rosalind Chatto said Scofield died yesterday in a hospital near his home in England. He had been suffering from leukaemia.                                                                                                                                                                              
